02:00:33.160 --> 02:00:40.360
longstanding UFO legacy crash retrieval program. You have one guy who's come out publicly and has

02:00:40.360 --> 02:00:42.120
not changed his story since 89.

02:00:42.120 --> 02:00:42.520
Well, I know.

02:00:42.520 --> 02:00:47.400
We didn't really know too much about the existence of Area 51, definitely not S4.

02:00:47.400 --> 02:00:48.120
He's never been there.

02:00:49.000 --> 02:00:52.040
But how would he know about, you know, Janet Airlines, the flight there?

02:00:52.040 --> 02:00:56.920
Well, he worked at Los Alamos, and he worked at the Unclassified Logistic Support Facility over

02:00:56.920 --> 02:01:03.640
on McCarran, over on Sunset Boulevard next to, not Sunset Boulevard, Sunset Drive next to McCarran

02:01:03.640 --> 02:01:11.480
Airport. There's a row of light industrial buildings along Sunset Road. And McCarran is right across

02:01:11.480 --> 02:01:17.000
the street. So Kimber Meyer was there, EG&G Special Projects was like next door.

02:01:17.480 --> 02:01:23.400
So he didn't go because he didn't have clearances. His job was just a radiation health badge monitor.

02:01:23.400 --> 02:01:29.400
So people that get on the Janet flight to go to Area 51, he gives them their radiation badges.

02:01:29.800 --> 02:01:33.320
When they come home from work, they get off that Janet flight, they got to give them back,

02:01:33.480 --> 02:01:37.800
give those badges back to him. And his job is to check those badges every day to make sure that

02:01:37.800 --> 02:01:38.120
they're working.

02:01:38.120 --> 02:01:42.920
Okay, but he's not a theoretical physicist, but he does have engineering chops. Like he runs

02:01:42.920 --> 02:01:46.640
currently United Nuclear. He literally put a jet engine on the tobacco.

02:01:46.640 --> 02:01:51.840
Yeah, I know. That's just a tinkerer. He's a hobbyist. He's also been twice convicted of

02:01:51.840 --> 02:01:53.040
felonies, including...

02:01:53.040 --> 02:01:55.040
Yeah, this isn't, guys...

02:01:55.040 --> 02:01:55.680
He's a nutcase.

02:01:55.680 --> 02:01:59.600
I have no interest in Bob Lazar the person. The key question is,

02:01:59.600 --> 02:02:03.120
if he was proximate to information that he garbled, is it possible...

02:02:03.120 --> 02:02:10.480
Is it possible to take the garbled message and associate QCD with two sectors, a Yang-Mills

02:02:10.480 --> 02:02:15.920
sector and a Pontryagin sector, and that the Chernvape representation of the Pontryagin

02:02:15.920 --> 02:02:22.400
sector inside of QCD associated with the theta term can lead to something which has Einstein-like

02:02:22.400 --> 02:02:23.600
properties, which is that they differentiate...

02:02:23.600 --> 02:02:24.800
That would be remarkable.

02:02:24.800 --> 02:02:26.000
That would be remarkable, right?

02:02:26.000 --> 02:02:29.600
That would be absolutely remarkable. The vacuum energy of QCD is impendous.

02:02:29.600 --> 02:02:33.920
So the thing that I'm... So let's get into vacuum energy and zero-point and what the source

02:02:33.920 --> 02:02:41.360
of energy is for all of these things. I'm very turned off by certain attempts to mine...

02:02:42.720 --> 02:02:48.320
Like if you look at the Heisenberg uncertainty relations, one of the great innovations in our time

02:02:48.320 --> 02:02:56.480
is that they've been associated to the symplectic form on phase space in ordinarily classical

02:02:56.480 --> 02:03:03.040
Hamiltonian dynamics. In other words, you take the space of configurations of a mug on a table,

02:03:03.040 --> 02:03:11.600
then you add the momenta, so that doubles the space, its size to go from configuration space to

02:03:11.600 --> 02:03:17.920
phase space, position to position and momenta. On that space, there's a guaranteed object called the

02:03:17.920 --> 02:03:25.680
symplectic form that comes just out of the math. The big innovation was to say, you know, that thing

02:03:26.720 --> 02:03:33.280
is actually at the base of a different structure called a line bundle, and it's the curvature tensor

02:03:33.840 --> 02:03:40.720
for this line bundle with a connection whose sections form the Hilbert space in quantization.

02:03:40.720 --> 02:03:42.560
Effectively, in a certain sense...

02:03:42.560 --> 02:03:43.600
Do you mean fiber bundle?

02:03:43.600 --> 02:03:50.720
Well, yeah, it's a line bundle, exactly. That that line bundle, it's L2 sections properly taken,

02:03:50.720 --> 02:03:57.200
polarized, there's a whole rigmarole, sort of self-quantize the manifold. In other words,

02:03:57.200 --> 02:04:06.320
that the classical mechanics leads naturally to the quantum theory when you realize it's not an isolated

02:04:06.320 --> 02:04:10.880
degree two object, but a degree two object that comes as the curvature of something else that we

02:04:10.880 --> 02:04:17.280
had not thought to study. If that's the source of the Heisenberg uncertainty relations, that's a

02:04:17.280 --> 02:04:24.400
curvature you can't get rid of. So if you try to mine it, I don't really see how you extract

02:04:26.960 --> 02:04:33.600
from something that can't be lessened. On the other hand, were you to try to tap into the dark energy,

02:04:33.600 --> 02:04:40.720
if that is in fact a VEV, a vacuum expectation value, rather than a hard constant? Could that be

02:04:40.720 --> 02:04:43.760
used as a on-demand power source?

02:04:43.760 --> 02:04:44.640
Sure could be.

02:04:44.640 --> 02:04:46.720
Do you work on that at all?

02:04:46.720 --> 02:04:54.000
No, but I looked at people who've sent me their ruminations on that idea, and it looked pretty

02:04:54.000 --> 02:04:58.800
intelligent, but it wasn't very well developed in my opinion. So I think that would be a great

02:04:58.800 --> 02:05:01.520
direction to go, and I like where you're going here.

02:05:01.520 --> 02:05:04.160
I'm just trying to be constructive. Let me try another one on you.

02:05:04.160 --> 02:05:06.960
Yeah, I like where you're going. I think you pointed out some stuff I'm not aware of,

02:05:06.960 --> 02:05:12.400
other than the dark energy aspect, which I'm already aware of, which need to be followed up on.

02:05:12.400 --> 02:05:20.320
Imagine for the moment that you embed what we currently call space-time in its space of all

02:05:20.320 --> 02:05:25.600
point-wise Lorentzian metrics. So every way you could possibly have of measuring length and angle

02:05:25.600 --> 02:05:30.880
through a series of three rulers, one watch, and six protractors.

02:05:33.920 --> 02:05:38.960
That's a 14-dimensional object that I work with on a daily basis that I call the observers. We don't

02:05:38.960 --> 02:05:42.320
have to get too far into this, but the point that I want to make is the following.

02:05:43.840 --> 02:05:49.280
There are ways of traveling through time and space, and I want to say also that time really

02:05:49.280 --> 02:05:54.720
should always be times because the number of actual temporal dimensions we currently think is one,

02:05:54.720 --> 02:05:56.160
one, but it doesn't need to be one.

02:05:56.160 --> 02:05:57.120
I agree.

02:05:57.120 --> 02:05:57.600
Okay.

02:06:00.880 --> 02:06:03.360
We talk a lot about entanglement. We talk a lot about

02:06:04.320 --> 02:06:07.440
wormholes. We don't talk about pinch to zoom.

02:06:07.440 --> 02:06:08.880
We don't talk about what?

02:06:08.880 --> 02:06:15.280
Pinch to zoom. Imagine that you pointed at a star that you wanted to visit,

02:06:16.400 --> 02:06:21.200
and imagine that you could find some way of traveling in 10 transverse dimensions.

02:06:21.200 --> 02:06:22.480
Okay.

02:06:22.480 --> 02:06:28.800
Where what you're doing is growing the ruler in the direction between you and that star.

02:06:28.800 --> 02:06:36.400
Now, once the ruler says one foot, you need the energy to walk one foot.

02:06:36.400 --> 02:06:36.880
Right.

02:06:36.880 --> 02:06:39.280
Not the energy to walk four light years.

02:06:39.280 --> 02:06:39.680
Right.

02:06:40.800 --> 02:06:43.600
And then you have to put the ruler back, so you have to shrink the ruler

02:06:44.240 --> 02:06:47.520
to grow the distance after you've grown the ruler to shrink the distance.

02:06:47.520 --> 02:06:47.920
Okay.

02:06:47.920 --> 02:06:52.880
So the idea is that this is something like pinch to zoom, which doesn't work on an ordinary table,

02:06:52.880 --> 02:06:58.880
but if this was a smart table, it would be what's called a multi-touch gesture.

02:07:00.240 --> 02:07:04.560
Have you thought about whether multi-touch gestures like pinch to zoom or another one

02:07:04.560 --> 02:07:09.680
that I call shear to tilt might be built into the object that we confuse for space-time?

02:07:09.680 --> 02:07:17.200
It sounds plausible. I like that. I've seen hints of something like that in some books I've read

02:07:17.200 --> 02:07:23.840
back in the 90s, very small hints of it. And I thought there was something to it that I just

02:07:23.840 --> 02:07:31.440
didn't follow up on. Yeah. I would say that makes sense. That makes sense to me. Yeah.

02:07:31.440 --> 02:07:39.360
Yeah. That's a very interesting idea. Do you think much about dark chemistry?

02:07:40.080 --> 02:07:40.800
About which?

02:07:40.800 --> 02:07:42.240
Dark chemistry.

02:07:42.240 --> 02:07:43.280
Dark chemistry.

02:07:43.280 --> 02:07:44.880
Like chemistry with dark matter.

02:07:44.880 --> 02:07:45.760
No, I don't.

02:07:49.040 --> 02:07:49.840
I see.

