Okay.

02:08:58.560 --> 02:09:01.360
And we move through time allegedly in one direction.

02:09:01.360 --> 02:09:06.880
So David Grush, I believe, used this phrase in a hearing, and they talked about holography.

02:09:06.880 --> 02:09:08.640
Yeah, Dave's not a physicist.

02:09:08.640 --> 02:09:11.200
I understand that. So what I'm trying to-

02:09:11.200 --> 02:09:15.280
Look, again, the point isn't to say whether somebody knows what they're talking about,

02:09:15.280 --> 02:09:22.480
but to say, assume that somebody does- assume that the plumber comes to you and says, wow,

02:09:22.480 --> 02:09:26.640
I was just at some crazy base, and I don't even know what these words mean,

02:09:26.640 --> 02:09:31.040
but here's what I heard, right? So very often, I'm just trying to- I'm not- I don't care about-

02:09:31.040 --> 02:09:36.560
Yeah, I think he's heard that from his briefings given to- from the briefings given to him on

02:09:36.560 --> 02:09:42.720
the crash retrieval program. I just, you know, he can't tell me that level of information at the

