another weird story where he's got patents for nuclear submarines, nuclear planes, nuclear shopping,

02:12:11.200 --> 02:12:18.240
I don't know what. Are aerospace companies something that we don't understand, where people actually did

02:12:18.240 --> 02:12:27.280
basic physics research, not material science, not something that's plane or rocket or drone adjacent, but

02:12:28.320 --> 02:12:29.760
where people were doing actual

02:12:32.240 --> 02:12:34.240
frontier research in fundamental physics?

02:12:34.240 --> 02:12:39.120
No, they wouldn't do that. Not in that, not in that industry.

02:12:39.120 --> 02:12:40.640
So they wouldn't use it as a shell?

02:12:40.640 --> 02:12:47.200
No, they do applied physics research. They're developing technical solutions to the government

02:12:47.200 --> 02:12:53.680
customer's request to answer the government customer's need for a solution to some problem.

02:12:53.680 --> 02:12:59.520
So it doesn't go to fundamental physics like, should we worry about these type of quarks versus

02:12:59.520 --> 02:13:04.720
those type of quarks? No, no, no. They're looking at a physics that could be applied to the engineering

02:13:04.720 --> 02:13:09.360
of a technological solution for the government customer. That's what the aerospace industry does.

02:13:09.360 --> 02:13:15.440
Oh, I understand what it's supposed to do. What I'm trying to say is, is it a system of containers

02:13:16.320 --> 02:13:21.600
and you can put anything in a container? I mean, in other words, you could imagine that if a container

02:13:21.600 --> 02:13:28.080
was secure, you could put a drug laundering, you know, money laundering, a drug operation inside of

02:13:28.080 --> 02:13:31.280
it. We wouldn't think, oh, that's what you'd expect to find it. That's right. Yeah.

02:13:31.280 --> 02:13:37.760
That it's like something crawled into that shell. My question is, is it possible that theoretical physics

02:13:38.400 --> 02:13:45.120
was sort of relocated into aerospace companies? Because this is a partially-

02:13:45.120 --> 02:13:49.040
I wouldn't say no to that. That's possible. That's possible.

02:13:49.040 --> 02:13:54.400
Uh, when we spoke to Hal Puthoff, he said, definitively, he said, you know, um, I don't,

02:13:54.400 --> 02:13:58.960
not sure about fundamental physics being tied up in aerospace corporations, but he goes topological

02:13:58.960 --> 02:14:05.440
physics, like probably. And he said, it, it, it would seem to me that physics generally is held in

02:14:05.440 --> 02:14:10.480
these aerospace, uh, companies. And, uh, you know, that was very, it made your sort of blood boil.

02:14:10.480 --> 02:14:15.840
Well, I worked for the aerospace corporation for four and a half years. I was one of only

02:14:15.840 --> 02:14:24.880
a dozen or so physicists with PhDs in the company of 4,000 employees.

02:14:26.160 --> 02:14:27.120
Which location?

02:14:27.120 --> 02:14:29.360
Uh, I was at Huntsville, Alabama.

02:14:29.360 --> 02:14:29.920
Okay.

02:14:29.920 --> 02:14:35.600
Because I was supporting the NASA space nuclear propulsion program office. So, uh, I was only

02:14:35.600 --> 02:14:40.880
one of maybe a dozen, maybe two. I don't think it was more than two, but definitely within two dozen

02:14:40.880 --> 02:14:46.160
PhD physicists in the whole country, in the whole company. And I'll have to tell you that

02:14:46.160 --> 02:14:51.600
not a single one, few of us were doing any physics. We were doing engineering work.

02:14:51.600 --> 02:14:54.720
And how many of you were trained in front, trained in frontier theory?

02:14:56.000 --> 02:14:57.920
Frontier theory. What do you mean?

02:14:57.920 --> 02:14:59.200
Standard model in GR.

02:14:59.200 --> 02:15:00.800
Oh, I didn't know.

02:15:00.800 --> 02:15:02.880
How far back from the front lines were you guys?

02:15:02.880 --> 02:15:08.240
I knew those guys and none of them were. Some of them were trained in astrodynamics,

02:15:08.240 --> 02:15:13.840
so they know general relativity and Newtonian mechanics. Uh, I'm the only one I know of who's

02:15:13.840 --> 02:15:17.920
been trained on the standard model in GR. I don't, I didn't know any of those other

02:15:17.920 --> 02:15:23.920
guys that work. There's one guy at Blue Origin who went to my university, got his PhD in general

02:15:23.920 --> 02:15:24.720
relativity theory.

02:15:24.720 --> 02:15:26.640
Is it University of Arizona Tucson?

02:15:26.640 --> 02:15:28.880
Two years after I got my doctorate.

02:15:28.880 --> 02:15:29.360
Okay.

02:15:29.360 --> 02:15:32.160
And he's working as an engineer at Blue Origin.

02:15:32.160 --> 02:15:39.280
Okay. Last question. I can't wrap my head around this. If I was facing an incursion in my

02:15:39.280 --> 02:15:46.240
airspace claiming craft that defy the laws of physics, and I didn't have a single top physicist

02:15:46.240 --> 02:15:51.440
on my team, I would expect to be fired instantly.

02:15:51.440 --> 02:15:55.920
Oh, sure. But that's not how they think. They don't think in terms of that. They're thinking

02:15:55.920 --> 02:16:02.480
in terms of their bottom line, and their bottom line will not involve a theoretical physicist.

02:16:02.480 --> 02:16:03.520
They might have-

02:16:03.520 --> 02:16:07.520
Sorry. What? You have craft the claim.

02:16:07.520 --> 02:16:09.280
They're engineers. I know, they're engineers.

02:16:09.280 --> 02:16:10.080
Okay, but if you-

02:16:10.080 --> 02:16:14.240
They're not thinking in terms of fundamental physics or something beyond the standard

02:16:14.240 --> 02:16:16.720
model or something beyond general relativity, they're thinking-

02:16:16.720 --> 02:16:21.920
How are they doing on this project decades in, the supposed project? How are they doing on it?

02:16:22.640 --> 02:16:23.520
What's their level of success?

02:16:23.520 --> 02:16:24.960
Oh, all I know is as of my knowledge-

02:16:24.960 --> 02:16:27.120
Okay. If you're failing at something-

02:16:27.120 --> 02:16:28.000
Yeah, they have success.

02:16:28.000 --> 02:16:32.880
...that requires new physics, you say, defy the laws of physics. We can't make progress,

02:16:32.880 --> 02:16:33.440
and we have no physicists.

02:16:33.440 --> 02:16:34.400
Correct. That's because they don't have-

02:16:34.400 --> 02:16:43.520
David, Eric, this can't add up. It's a two-line proof. It defies the laws of physics. We haven't

02:16:43.520 --> 02:16:50.320
made progress. We have no physicists. If something defies the laws of physics, who do you call?

02:16:51.760 --> 02:16:59.040
I know, you ask any of us, any of us, write down 15 names of who you call if you had a craft that

02:16:59.040 --> 02:17:04.240
defied the laws of physics. Wait a second. 12 of those names, 10 of those names would be the same

02:17:04.240 --> 02:17:05.360
on everybody's list.

02:17:05.360 --> 02:17:05.680
Okay.

02:17:07.680 --> 02:17:14.320
The final thing I would say is, if Hal Puthoff was telling us that some physics is held,

02:17:14.320 --> 02:17:18.400
whether it's, even if it's just experimental physics, you have a bunch of people over the

02:17:18.400 --> 02:17:25.440
last 70 years, the foremost in my mind, Townsend Brown, and you know, this Ning Li at University

02:17:25.440 --> 02:17:29.280
of Alabama, Huntsville, saying that they're getting little weight reduction effects,

02:17:29.280 --> 02:17:30.400
gravitational shielding, something.

02:17:30.400 --> 02:17:34.320
Well, that's wrong. They didn't. They were incompetent. There is no weight reduction.

02:17:34.320 --> 02:17:37.680
So, simultaneously, Hal's thing of there being-

02:17:37.680 --> 02:17:40.560
Look at the two chapters in my book on the Townsend-Brown effect.

